.TH "mark_bbt_region" 9 "mark_bbt_region" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mark_bbt_region \- [GENERIC] mark the bad block table regions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" mark_bbt_region
.BI "(struct nand_chip *this "  ","
.BI "struct nand_bbt_descr *td "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "this" 12
the NAND device
.IP "td" 12
bad block table descriptor
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The bad block table regions are marked as "bad" to prevent accidental
erasures / writes. The regions are identified by the mark 0x02.
